TITLE: Defining Backend Method in Remult Controller
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define a backend method in a Remult controller using the @BackendMethod decorator. It includes parameter validation and error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/interactive/src/content/tutorial/1-basics/6-backend-methods/meta.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
@BackendMethod({ allowed: true })
async resetPassword(userId: string, newPassword: string) {
  const user = await this.repo.findId(userId);
  if (!user) {
    throw new Error("User not found");
  }
  user.password = newPassword;
  await user.save();
}
```

