TITLE: Implementing Custom Validation in Remult Entity
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to implement custom validation logic in a Remult entity using the validate method. It checks for unique usernames and performs other validations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/interactive/src/content/tutorial/1-basics/4-validation/meta.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
@Entity("users")
export class User {
  @Fields.string()
  id!: string;

  @Fields.string()
  username = "";

  @Fields.string()
  name = "";

  async validate() {
    if (this.username.length < 3)
      throw "Username too short";
    const exists = await repo(User).count({
      username: this.username,
      id: { $ne: this.id }
    });
    if (exists > 0)
      throw "Username already taken";
  }
}
```

