TITLE: Implementing Raw SQL Custom Filter in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates creating a custom filter using raw SQL to query orders based on customer city and year. Uses parameterized queries for SQL injection prevention.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/docs/custom-filter.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
static activeOrders = Filter.createCustom<
  Order,
  { year: number; customerCity: string }
>(async ({ year, customerCity }) => {
  return {
    status: ["created", "confirmed", "pending", "blocked", "delayed"],
    createdAt: {
      $gte: new Date(year, 0, 1),
      $lt: new Date(year + 1, 0, 1),
    },
    $and: [
      SqlDatabase.rawFilter(({param}) =>  
        `"customerId" in (select id from customers where city = ${param(customerCity)})` 
      ), 
    ],
  }
})
```

