TITLE: Enhanced SQL-Based Filter Using dbNamesOf and filterToRaw
DESCRIPTION: A more maintainable version of the SQL custom filter that uses dbNamesOf and filterToRaw to leverage entity definitions in the query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/docs/filtering-and-relations.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { dbNamesOf } from 'remult'

@Entity('orders', { allowApiCrud: true })
export class Order {
  //...
  static filterCity = Filter.createCustom<Order, { city: string }>(
    async ({ city }) => {
      const orders = await dbNamesOf(Order)
      const customers = await dbNamesOf(Customer)
      return SqlDatabase.rawFilter(
        async ({ filterToRaw }) =>
          `${orders.customer} in 
               (select ${customers.id} 
                  from ${customers} 
                 where ${await filterToRaw(Customer, { city })})`,
      )
    },
  )
}
```

