TITLE: Implementing Saving and Deleting Hooks for Task Entity in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the implementation of saving and deleting hooks for a Task entity in Remult. The saving hook logs new tasks and field changes for existing tasks, while the deleting hook logs the title of tasks being deleted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/interactive/src/content/tutorial/4-concepts/8-entities-as-a-single-source-of-truth/3-lifecycle-events/content.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
@Entity<Task>("tasks", {
    saving: (task, e) => {
        if (e.isNew) {
            console.log(`New task: ${task.title}`);
        } else {
            for (const field of e.fields) {
                if (field.valueChanged()) {
                    console.log(
                        `${field.metadata.caption} changed from ${field.originalValue} to ${field.value}`
                    );
                }
            }
        }
    },
    deleting: (task) => {
        console.log(`Deleting task: ${task.title}`);
    },
})
export class Task {
    // ... rest of the Task class definition
}
```

