TITLE: Bootstrapping Remult in Nest.js main.ts
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to set up the main entry point for a Nest.js application with Remult integration. It creates a Nest.js application, integrates Remult as middleware, and starts the server on port 3002.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/docs/installation/server/nest.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// src/main.ts

import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core'
import { AppModule } from './app.module'
import { remultExpress } from 'remult/remult-express'

async function bootstrap() {
  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule)

  app.use(remultExpress()) // Integrate Remult as middleware

  await app.listen(3002) // Start server on port 3002
}
bootstrap()
```

