TITLE: Using Existing Knex Provider with Remult
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use an existing Knex provider with Remult. It demonstrates creating a Knex instance and passing it to the KnexDataProvider.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remult/remult/blob/main/docs/docs/quickstart.md#2025-04-16_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import express from 'express'
import { KnexDataProvider } from 'remult/remult-knex'
import { remultExpress } from 'remult/remult-express'
import knex from 'knex'

const knexDb = knex({
  client: '...',
  connection: '...',
})

const app = express()

app.use(
  remultExpress({
    dataProvider: new KnexDataProvider(knexDb), // [!code highlight]
  }),
)
```

